main event: Several black and white photographs were documented displaying unidentified luminous objects in the night sky during October 2-15, 1966.
interesting points: The photographs vary in clarity and depict objects that are round or oval-shaped, arranged in formations,The report includes a total of 15 photographs, although no human figures are visible in any of them,The objects appear as bright spots against a dark background, indicating possible UFO activity,The report is associated with the Foreign Technology Division, AFSC, and is marked as UNCLASSIFIED,Some of the photographs are noted to be grainy, suggesting they are older or historical.
sighted object: unidentified luminous objects in the night sky
witness description: No human faces or individuals identified in the photographs
